title: Bug 114470[Smoke] Error message throws when using new Date("3/2/2005") as value in table filter.
OB: When using the value new Date("3/2/2005") in the table filter, error messages are displayed on the report page. The error message states that there is an error in the table (table8) related to data conversion. The error mentions a data.engine.DataConversionError and indicates that the value cannot be converted to a date.
EB: When using the value new Date("3/2/2005") in the table filter, there should be no errors. The filter should work as expected without any data conversion errors.
SR:
1. Open the report.
2. Apply a filter using the value new Date("3/2/2005").
3. Save and preview the report.
4. Observe the error messages on the report page.
